     <scan style="font-family: 'Georgia'; font-variant: small-caps; font-size: 80%; font-weight: bold; margin: 0 0 0.625% 0; padding:0; border:0; line-height:70%">Jun 2017- </scan><strong>2017 </strong>started off strong for the Canadian banks with six offerings by the ninth of January and two more in March. &nbspHowever, since then they have been quiet, with no issuance at all. &nbspCanadian 'bail-in' proposals have been <a href="http://www.fin.gc.ca/n17/17-057-eng.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">published</a> and that may account for some their absence from the market as they reconsider their funding strategies.
